     <em>
      atg
     </em>
     genes (
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ;
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ), Bad (siRNA1 from
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ; siRNA2: CUGGGCAGCCAUCUUGAAU dTdT), Vps (siRNA1 from
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     and siRNA2 from
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ), a scrambled siRNA or an siRNA targeting the unrelated protein emerin (
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ). siRNA effects were controlled by immunoblots with suitable antibodies specific for Beclin-1 (SantaCruz), Bad (SantaCruz) or Vps34 (Zymed). Transient transfections with cDNAs were performed with Lipofectamine 2000 reagent (Invitrogen), and cells were used 24 h after transfection unless specified differently. Cells were transfected with empty vector alone or together with LC3-GFP (
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ), in the presence or absence of Beclin-1 wild type, Beclin-1 L116A, Beclin-1 F123A, Bcl-X
     <sub>
      L
     </sub>
     wild type, Bcl-X
     <sub>
      L
     </sub>
     G138A, Bcl-2 wild type, or Mcl-1.
    </p>
   </sec>
