     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      None
     </xref>
     ). Each screen was performed to ensure a minimum of 50 million interactions. The prey fragments of the positive clones were amplified by PCR and sequenced at their 5′ and 3′ junctions on a PE3700 Sequencer. The resulting sequences were used to identify the corresponding gene in the GenBank database (NCBI).
